# M3 Memory — Example Environment
#
# Copy to .env and set your local values. Every var below is OPTIONAL: m3 runs
# with zero configuration (sensible defaults shown). Precedence and the full
# variable reference live in docs/ENVIRONMENT_VARIABLES.md.
#
# NOTE: The MCP server does NOT inherit your shell environment — it reads only
# the `env` block in your client's settings.json. A var set here (or in your
# shell) reaches CLI/hook invocations, but for the running MCP server it must
# also be in that server env block. See docs/ENVIRONMENT_VARIABLES.md
# ("split-brain hazard").

# ── Roots (decoupled state; see docs/ENVIRONMENT_VARIABLES.md) ────────────────
# Precedence for each root: its own var > M3_MEMORY_ROOT-derived > default.
# M3_MEMORY_ROOT is the master override (config -> <root>/config, engine ->
# <root>/engine) unless the specific root var below is set.
#M3_MEMORY_ROOT=            # default: ~/.m3-memory
#M3_CONFIG_ROOT=            # default: ~/.m3/config   (.chatlog_config.json, salt, ...)
#M3_ENGINE_ROOT=            # default: ~/.m3/engine   (agent_memory.db, chatlog, spill)

# ── Database ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Overrides the resolved default (<engine_root>/agent_memory.db) for ALL calls.
# Per-call override: pass `database` to any MCP tool. Precedence:
# explicit arg > M3_DATABASE > active-db contextvar > default.
#M3_DATABASE=

# ── Embedding (local-first; bge-m3 is canonical) ─────────────────────────────
# Tier-1 in-process GGUF embedder (fastest). If unset, auto-detected from LM
# Studio model dirs (M3_EMBED_GGUF_AUTODETECT=1 by default). Pin it to be
# explicit / for headless deployments where the model lives elsewhere.
#M3_EMBED_GGUF=/path/to/bge-m3-GGUF-Q4_K_M.gguf
#EMBED_MODEL=text-embedding-bge-m3      # default (do NOT use a nomic model)
#M3_EMBED_FALLBACK_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8082   # tier-2 CPU HTTP embed service

# ── Tool call timeout ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default per-call timeout for every MCP tool, seconds. Per-call override: pass
# `timeout` to any tool. <=0 disables. Default: 30.
#M3_TOOL_TIMEOUT=30

# ── Optional external tier (L2 Postgres sync) ────────────────────────────────
# Opt-in; m3 is fully functional on SQLite alone.
#POSTGRES_SERVER=your.server.host
#SYNC_TARGET_IP=your.server.host

# ── Secrets: use the OS keychain, NOT this file ──────────────────────────────
# API keys and PG_URL belong in your OS keyring / m3 vault, never in .env:
#   python bin/auth_utils.py set PG_URL "postgresql://user:pass@host:port/db"
#   python bin/auth_utils.py set LM_API_TOKEN "..."
